Task:
Build a simple JavaScript web app that: 
Uses the Yelp API to fetch restaurants for a given city
Has a basic web UI where a user can input a city and see results
Displays a clean, accurate list of restaurants

Requirements:
Use real Yelp API data (no mock data)
Results should be relevant to the city (within city limits or 5-mile radius)
Keep the solution simple and clean, avoid overengineering
Display: name, rating, address, and coordinates
UI can be minimal, but should be functional and easy to use

Submission:
Share a live demo link (preferred) or clear instructions to run locally
Provide your code (GitHub or file)
Include a short explanation (3–5 sentences) of your approach
Briefly explain how you handled accuracy and edge cases